              <div class="xsv-faq" style="width:100%;margin-left: -20px;margin-bottom:-20px;max-width:none;">
                <h1>FAQ</h1>
                <div class="xsv-faq-group">
                  <div class="xsv-faq-header">
                    <i class="icon-accordion-toggle icon-chevron-right"></i>
                    <span class="xsv-faq-question">
                      What is <i>User Defined</i> context creation?
                    </span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="xsv-faq-body" style="display:none;">
                    The user specifies all of the values necessary to create a context.
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="xsv-faq-group">
                  <div class="xsv-faq-header">
                    <i class="icon-accordion-toggle icon-chevron-right"></i>
                    <span class="xsv-faq-question">
                      What is <i>Data Driven</i> context creation?
                    </span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="xsv-faq-body" style="display:none;">
                    The user specifies a search that will generate the values necessary to create a context.
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="xsv-faq-group">
                  <div class="xsv-faq-header">
                    <i class="icon-accordion-toggle icon-chevron-right"></i>
                    <span class="xsv-faq-question">
                      What is <i>Crossover Driven</i> context creation?
                    </span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="xsv-faq-body" style="display:none;">
                    The user specifies the crossover points (boundaries) between concepts in a context. A crossover point is the point where membersip in the intersecting concepts is equal (0.5).
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="xsv-faq-group">
                  <div class="xsv-faq-header">
                    <i class="icon-accordion-toggle icon-chevron-right"></i>
                    <span class="xsv-faq-question">
                      What is <i>Anomaly Driven</i> context creation?
                    </span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="xsv-faq-body" style="display:none;">
                      The user specifies the crossover points (boundaries) where data becomes more anomalous than normal, or more normal than anomalous.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
