                <div class="xsv-faq" style="width:100%;margin-left: -20px;margin-bottom:-20px;max-width:none;">
                  <h1>FAQ</h1>
                  <div class="xsv-faq-group">
                    <div class="xsv-faq-header">
                      <i class="icon-accordion-toggle icon-chevron-right"></i>
                      <span class="xsv-faq-question">
                        What are the min and max parameters for a domain context?
                      </span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="xsv-faq-body" style="display:none;">
                      In a “domain" context, the context range is from the min to the max values and the individual concepts will be distributed evenly across that domain.  If the method for creating the context is “User Defined”, then the user must specify these values; otherwise the min and max values will be determined from the data in a search.
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="xsv-faq-group">
                    <div class="xsv-faq-header">
                      <i class="icon-accordion-toggle icon-chevron-right"></i>
                      <span class="xsv-faq-question">
                        What are the average, size and width paramters for an average centered context?
                      </span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="xsv-faq-body" style="display:none;">
                      In an “average centered" context, the context will be centered on the average. The width and size parameters determine the context range and the individual concept sizes will be scaled across that range. The width parameter corresponds to standard deviation and the size parameter is a multiplier.  If the method for creating the context is not “User Defined”, then these parameters are derived from the data in a search. The product of these two parameters determine the context range.
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="xsv-faq-group">
                    <div class="xsv-faq-header">
                      <i class="icon-accordion-toggle icon-chevron-right"></i>
                      <span class="xsv-faq-question">
                        What are the median, size, and width paramters for a median centered context?
                      </span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="xsv-faq-body" style="display:none;">
                      In a “Median Centered” context, the context will be centered on the median. The width and size parameters determine the context range and the individual concept sizes will be scaled across that range. The width parameter corresponds to standard deviation and the size parameter is a multiplier.  If the method for creating the context is not “User Defined”, then these parameters are derived from the data in a search. The product of these two parameters determine the context range.
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div id="dataDefined" style="display:none;">
                <label>You selected <i>Data Driven</i> context creation method. Enter a search command to obtain data and a statics command to generate range parameters for the selected <i><span id="selectedType"></span></i> context type.<span id="range-datadefined-error-msg" class="xsv-error-message"></span></label>
                <div class="control-group wizard-box">
                  <div class="inner-wizard-box">
                    <div class="control-group">
                      <label>* Search Command: </label>
                      <textarea rows="4" id="searchTA" style="width:250px;display:block;margin-top:10px;"></textarea>
                    </div>
                    <div class="control-group">
	              <input id="statsCB" type="checkbox" name="statsCB" value="true" aria-label="..." style="margin-bottom:8px;" >
                        <span style="margin-left:10px;">Apply Stats Command using Field: <input id="fieldTI" type="text" style="display:block;"/></span>
                      </input>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="control-group wizard-box">
                  <div class="inner-wizard-box">
                    <div id="statsDefined" style="display:none;">
                      <div class="control-group">
                        <label>* Stats Command: </label>
                        <textarea rows="4" id="statsTA" style="display:block;margin-top:10px;height:130px;width:250px;"></textarea>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
